WEBVTT

00:01.001 --> 00:03.137
You're witnessing
the power of Empire.

00:03.171 --> 00:05.706
I'm Cookie Lyon, baby.
I'm unforgettable.

00:05.739 --> 00:07.308
Catch all-new episodes
Wednesdays.

00:07.341 --> 00:08.976
And check out
our other Fox programs--

00:09.009 --> 00:11.812
Star, The Gifted,
and Lethal Weapon.

00:11.845 --> 00:14.415
That was the best idea
you've had all day.

00:14.448 --> 00:15.583
Only on Fox.

00:18.619 --> 00:20.088
-Previously on Empire...
-Are you saying Mr. Barker

00:20.121 --> 00:21.222
would come on board at Empire?

00:21.255 --> 00:23.491
Special advisor to your CEO,
Cookie Lyon.

00:23.524 --> 00:26.927
And when I didn't quit
my job for you, you dumped me.

00:26.960 --> 00:30.064
This court awards full custody
to Anika Calhoun.

00:30.098 --> 00:31.565
-ANIKA: Yes! (laughs)
-(gavel bangs)

00:31.599 --> 00:33.567
-Warren, what are you
doing here? -DIANA: My nephew

00:33.601 --> 00:34.702
can provide full details.

00:34.735 --> 00:37.105
Your nephew? Bitch!

00:37.138 --> 00:39.607
-WARREN: She ruined me.
-ANGELO: You ruined you.

00:39.640 --> 00:42.243
I told you what would happen
if you fell for a Lyon.

00:42.276 --> 00:44.212
She compromised my therapist?

00:44.245 --> 00:45.846
Yeah, see, he was
messing with your meds

00:45.879 --> 00:47.215
so he could mess with your mind.

00:47.248 --> 00:50.118
I'm Vegas Metro. I got you.

00:50.151 --> 00:52.386
-(shouting)
-(grunting)

00:52.420 --> 00:55.022
COOKIE: There is nobody in here
but you and us.

00:55.055 --> 00:58.259
-There's nothing here, baby!
-Oh, no.

00:58.292 --> 01:00.361
You see what that bitch did
to my baby?

01:00.394 --> 01:02.263
ANDRE:
Oh, God!

01:02.296 --> 01:04.598
We coming for you, bitch.

01:06.900 --> 01:08.969
Funk Flex, I'm in the building.

01:09.002 --> 01:10.638
(crowd cheering)

01:10.671 --> 01:12.973
Y'all ready for this?

01:13.006 --> 01:17.145
Who has the number one album
on Empire?

01:17.178 --> 01:18.412
(cheering continues)

01:18.446 --> 01:22.483
The hottest single
on Empire XStream?

01:22.516 --> 01:25.586
The Lyon of all Lyons.

01:26.820 --> 01:29.757
The once and future king!

01:37.498 --> 01:40.100
*

01:40.134 --> 01:42.069
* To belong *

01:42.102 --> 01:44.605
* Yeah, yeah, yeah, yeah, yeah *

01:44.638 --> 01:46.240
* To belong *

01:46.274 --> 01:48.342
* Yeah, yeah, yeah, yeah, yeah *

01:48.376 --> 01:49.943
(crowd cheering)

01:49.977 --> 01:53.514
* Yeah, yeah, yeah, yeah, yeah *

01:53.547 --> 01:58.952
* Long ago

02:00.988 --> 02:05.859
* And oh so far away

02:05.893 --> 02:07.461
(Cookie whoops)

02:09.530 --> 02:15.836
* I fell in love
with you, baby *

02:18.138 --> 02:24.678
* Before the second show

02:26.747 --> 02:30.318
* Don't you remember
you told me *

02:30.351 --> 02:35.623
* You loved me, baby?

02:35.656 --> 02:37.858
* You said you'd be
coming back *

02:37.891 --> 02:41.362
* This way again, baby

02:43.931 --> 02:45.899
* Baby, baby

02:45.933 --> 02:48.068
* Baby

02:48.101 --> 02:52.039
-(whoops) Yes!
-* Oh, baby, baby...

02:53.841 --> 02:55.108
Pop?

02:57.578 --> 02:59.513
Pop?

03:01.782 --> 03:02.983
Pop?

03:03.016 --> 03:04.418
(music fades)

03:04.452 --> 03:06.987
Pop!

03:07.020 --> 03:08.756
Lucious!

03:08.789 --> 03:10.391
Pop!

03:12.226 --> 03:15.929
Pop...!

03:15.963 --> 03:17.498
(Andre grunting)

03:17.531 --> 03:18.899
LUCIOUS:
It's all right, son.

03:18.932 --> 03:21.101
It's all right. Daddy's here.

03:21.134 --> 03:23.103
It's okay. Daddy's here.

03:23.136 --> 03:24.938
Daddy's here. I got you.

03:24.972 --> 03:26.540
Daddy's got you now.

03:27.608 --> 03:29.843
Daddy's got you now.

03:29.877 --> 03:32.179
It's okay.

03:32.212 --> 03:33.847
It's gonna be fine.

03:33.881 --> 03:35.215
Hello, Mr. Lyon.

03:37.718 --> 03:40.120
-Can he hear me?
-Your son is

03:40.153 --> 03:42.890
pretty much in his own world
right now, Mr. Lyon,

03:42.923 --> 03:44.992
but I believe
he can sense your presence.

03:47.127 --> 03:48.962
His blood pressure stabilized

03:48.996 --> 03:51.399
the moment his mother
came in yesterday.

03:51.432 --> 03:53.934
She didn't want to leave.

03:53.967 --> 03:56.103
What's up with the straps?

03:56.136 --> 03:58.706
It's for his own safety,
Mr. Lyon.

03:58.739 --> 04:00.240
We're keeping Andre
heavily sedated

04:00.274 --> 04:02.876
while we purge the psychotropics
from his system.

04:02.910 --> 04:05.245
And then what?

04:05.279 --> 04:07.481
We won't be able to determine
whether he's suffered

04:07.515 --> 04:11.785
any permanent brain injury until
the drugs clear his system.

04:13.854 --> 04:18.926
You do understand
your son had a psychotic break?

04:18.959 --> 04:23.864
And you understand that my son's
gonna be perfectly fine, right?

04:32.440 --> 04:34.975
Andre.

04:35.008 --> 04:37.911
I want you to listen to me.

04:37.945 --> 04:40.080
I'm your daddy,

04:40.113 --> 04:42.282
and I'm back.

04:42.316 --> 04:45.419
Which means that the people
that did this to my boy

04:45.453 --> 04:48.121
is gonna pay dearly.

04:48.155 --> 04:51.825
Eye for eye, tooth for tooth,

04:51.859 --> 04:56.029
and bloody soul for bloody soul.

04:56.063 --> 04:57.998
*

05:03.070 --> 05:05.272
Juanita, do you have
my necklace?

05:05.305 --> 05:07.140
-JUANITA: Yes, ma'am.
-Thank you.

05:07.174 --> 05:09.176
It's gonna be great.

05:09.209 --> 05:11.345
Excuse me, Ms. Juanita,
I'm sure there's a...

05:11.379 --> 05:13.547
-(Cookie sighs) -...plate left
in the kitchen somewhere.

05:13.581 --> 05:15.949
Oh, what are you doing, Lucious?

05:15.983 --> 05:17.951
What God gave me to do.

05:17.985 --> 05:19.687
Oh, please, I got this.

05:19.720 --> 05:21.054
-(chuckles)
-Shh.

05:21.088 --> 05:23.190
So, come on. What's the plan?

05:23.223 --> 05:27.795
I know we got the Captain's Ball
and all this stuff to do,

05:27.828 --> 05:30.898
but, I mean, which one of these
Dubois can I get at?

05:30.931 --> 05:32.833
COOKIE:
Uh, no, no, no.

05:32.866 --> 05:34.835
I got it, Lucious,
'cause I can't risk

05:34.868 --> 05:37.471
you going all Dwight
on me and...

05:37.505 --> 05:39.072
ruining everything.
(chuckles)

05:39.106 --> 05:41.108
I don't even know who that is.

05:43.844 --> 05:46.146
COOKIE: Okay, let's talk
about this after Eddie's party.

05:46.179 --> 05:47.981
(chuckles) Stop.

05:48.015 --> 05:51.151
GAVIN: The Captain's Ball
begins promptly at 8:00,

05:51.184 --> 05:53.053
and we'll have
a veritable militia staged

05:53.086 --> 05:56.023
in the ballroom tonight guarding
the event from the inside.

05:56.056 --> 05:57.591
They're trained in discretion.

05:57.625 --> 05:59.393
Your guests will never know
they're there.

05:59.427 --> 06:02.329
So, you have vetted
all of the waitstaff,

06:02.362 --> 06:04.598
all of the hotel workers?

06:04.632 --> 06:07.835
Yes, ma'am. Nobody's getting
through the cracks.

06:07.868 --> 06:09.437
Very good. Thank you.

06:09.470 --> 06:11.071
-Thank you, gentlemen.
-Yes, ma'am.

06:11.104 --> 06:14.007
(men murmuring)

06:14.041 --> 06:15.943
Anika.

06:15.976 --> 06:18.378
I need you to check in
with the orchestra.

06:18.412 --> 06:20.848
I have ordered
a very specific program.

06:20.881 --> 06:22.916
I want Ellington and BC,

06:22.950 --> 06:26.520
and... Gershwin and Porter,
and my favorite, Schubert.

06:26.554 --> 06:27.521
Schubert.

06:27.555 --> 06:30.023
With pleasure, Diana.

06:30.057 --> 06:32.192
-I'm right on it.
-Thank you.

06:32.225 --> 06:34.928
Oh, and please check
the placement of video screens.

06:34.962 --> 06:36.897
I want everybody to enjoy
the film we've created

06:36.930 --> 06:39.767
about the Dubois
Philanthropic Foundation.

06:39.800 --> 06:41.502
-Consider it done.
-Thank you.

06:44.237 --> 06:47.240
Okay, Angelo. What is it?

06:47.274 --> 06:49.543
You sure you want
to go through with this?

06:49.577 --> 06:52.045
Have the Captain's Ball
when-when this war

06:52.079 --> 06:55.415
between our family and the Lyons
is-is so hot?

06:55.449 --> 06:57.551
(chuckles)
I'm not at war with anyone.

06:57.585 --> 07:01.154
But after last year's debacle,
it is time for us

07:01.188 --> 07:03.591
to differentiate
and distinguish ourselves

07:03.624 --> 07:06.393
so that people know who we are.

07:06.426 --> 07:09.630
You let one of those Lyons
show up here tonight,

07:09.663 --> 07:11.431
(scoffs)
they'll be carted away.

07:11.465 --> 07:13.400
Listen, I got to go.

07:13.433 --> 07:15.335
(sighs)

07:19.006 --> 07:21.475
*

07:23.477 --> 07:26.079
-It's fine.
-PORSHA: Look at these.

07:26.113 --> 07:27.447
Look how big these are.

07:27.481 --> 07:29.016
I ain't never seen them
this big.

07:29.049 --> 07:31.418
They need to start
calling them something else.

07:31.451 --> 07:33.420
-It's good, though.
-(Becky groans)

07:33.453 --> 07:35.088
-You okay?
-Mm-mm, mm-mm, mm-mm.

07:35.122 --> 07:37.290
-I'm sorry. I got to go.
-Hey, hold on, hold on, hold on.

07:37.324 --> 07:39.026
What's up, Becky?
You looking good, mama.

07:39.059 --> 07:40.761
You got this glow going on.

07:40.794 --> 07:41.862
-Okay.
-Hey, hold on, hold on.

07:41.895 --> 07:43.363
How come Andre's not here?

07:43.396 --> 07:44.965
I don't know, Shine.

07:44.998 --> 07:46.433
Where can I find him?

07:46.466 --> 07:48.301
I don't keep tabs
on all my superiors.

07:48.335 --> 07:50.938
Get out of my way.

07:50.971 --> 07:52.973
HAKEEM:
Two legends.

07:53.006 --> 07:54.508
-JAMAL: Mm-hmm.
-EDDIE: Mm-hmm.

07:54.542 --> 07:56.176
Can't believe you leaving us,
Uncle Eddie.

07:56.209 --> 07:57.511
You guys got to come
and visit me, all right?

07:57.545 --> 07:58.879
Definitely. Definitely.

07:58.912 --> 08:00.948
Y'all see them photos,
don't you?

08:00.981 --> 08:02.883
That's history there.

08:02.916 --> 08:04.718
Wouldn't have an Empire
if it wasn't for this man here.

08:04.752 --> 08:06.687
He's been there
from the beginning.

08:06.720 --> 08:09.156
You know you didn't have to do
all this for me, right?

08:09.189 --> 08:11.024
It's making me kind of sad
that I'm leaving.

08:11.058 --> 08:12.993
Then don't.

08:13.026 --> 08:15.062
Look, I...

08:15.095 --> 08:17.064
Almost finished
with Tiana's 20 For 20 album.

08:17.097 --> 08:18.899
A couple more sessions left.

08:18.932 --> 08:22.703
My mom always told me never
to overstay my welcome, and, uh,

08:22.736 --> 08:25.573
now that Lucious is back,
you guys don't need me no more.

08:25.606 --> 08:27.174
That's not true.

08:27.207 --> 08:29.176
(Cookie laughs)

08:29.209 --> 08:31.178
EDDIE: This is beautiful.
I'll tell you that?

08:31.211 --> 08:32.680
COOKIE:
Thank you.

08:32.713 --> 08:34.815
EDDIE: Jamal, what do you
say to your mom?

08:34.848 --> 08:35.916
JAMAL:
She looks lovely.

08:35.949 --> 08:37.484
COOKIE:
Thanks.

08:37.517 --> 08:39.486
-Little something I put
together. -Go ahead, Mama.

08:39.519 --> 08:41.088
Oh, there the Hand of God.
He's right there.

08:41.121 --> 08:42.055
Oh.

08:42.089 --> 08:45.392
EDDIE:
Look at him. He's back.

08:45.425 --> 08:47.027
COOKIE:
You really think he's back?

08:47.060 --> 08:49.362
What? You're not convinced?

08:49.396 --> 08:51.498
I don't know, Eddie.

08:51.531 --> 08:54.234
-I just don't know.
-Then let's find out.

08:54.267 --> 08:55.402
Lucious Lyon!

08:56.937 --> 08:58.338
Calling you out, man.

08:58.371 --> 09:00.507
Say when.

09:00.540 --> 09:04.377
Come get your ass down here and
let's go over in here, old head.

09:04.411 --> 09:06.880
I'm the baddest man
in the whole damn land.

09:06.914 --> 09:08.616
-Uh-oh. -And you want to do
some hair cutting?

09:08.649 --> 09:10.083
Y'all need to cut
this music down, all right?

09:10.117 --> 09:12.219
-Cut the music down.
-LUCIOUS: Hey, you know

09:12.252 --> 09:14.554
-I do this for a living, right?
-Uh-huh. Yeah, I do.

09:14.588 --> 09:17.958
And I thank you for letting me
have your seat for a little bit.

09:17.991 --> 09:20.460
-(chuckles)
-Oh, is that what this is?

09:20.493 --> 09:22.029
No, thank you. Hell no, man.

09:22.062 --> 09:23.396
What you got?

09:23.430 --> 09:25.232
I'm gonna do something
old school.

09:25.265 --> 09:27.100
-Let's do it for Cookie,
all right? -COOKIE: Uh-oh.

09:27.134 --> 09:28.268
For my Cookie.

09:28.301 --> 09:29.302
EDDIE:
Mm-hmm.

09:31.138 --> 09:33.073
*

09:38.278 --> 09:41.248
* You didn't have to love me
like you did *

09:41.281 --> 09:44.885
* But you did,
but you did, ha-ha *

09:44.918 --> 09:46.954
* And I thank you

09:46.987 --> 09:51.591
* Well, you didn't have
to squeeze me like you did *

09:51.625 --> 09:54.995
* But you did, but you did

09:55.028 --> 09:58.165
* And I thank you

09:58.198 --> 10:03.070
* If you took your love
to somewhere else *

10:03.103 --> 10:05.505
* I wouldn't know
what it meant *

10:05.538 --> 10:08.308
-* To be loved to death
-(Cookie laughs)

10:08.341 --> 10:13.580
* You made me feel
like I've never felt *

10:13.613 --> 10:17.617
* The kisses so good
I had to holler for help. *

10:23.791 --> 10:25.325
-Porsha? We're going to the
mattresses. Hey, boys. -Hey, Ma.

10:25.358 --> 10:26.927
Hold all my calls,
and let Thirsty know

10:26.960 --> 10:28.829
I'm ready to see him, please.

10:28.862 --> 10:31.198
Mattresses? What, you trying
to take a nap or something?

10:31.231 --> 10:33.133
Please leave the office, Porsha.
Thank you.

10:36.569 --> 10:39.973
So are you ready to take
your seat back on your throne?

10:40.007 --> 10:41.775
You mean the seat
that I've sat in

10:41.809 --> 10:43.510
for damn near two decades
building this company?

10:46.646 --> 10:48.882
Damn right
I'm gonna sit in my seat.

10:48.916 --> 10:50.751
You should sit in yours.

10:53.821 --> 10:55.055
Your throne.

10:59.993 --> 11:01.028
(chuckles softly)

11:01.061 --> 11:02.629
Thank you.

11:02.662 --> 11:03.864
You're the queen.

11:03.897 --> 11:06.166
What's the plan?

11:06.199 --> 11:08.902
Well, we found out that they're
gonna have their little party

11:08.936 --> 11:11.571
at the Carlton Marquis, but...

11:11.604 --> 11:14.374
you know security's
gonna be up the wazoo.

11:14.407 --> 11:16.509
(playing minor-key
classical music)

11:16.543 --> 11:18.411
Yeah, I don't know how
we're supposed to get in there.

11:18.445 --> 11:19.679
Ma, you got a plan?

11:19.713 --> 11:21.514
-THIRSTY: You ready for me,
Cook? -Right on time.

11:21.548 --> 11:23.851
Oh, it's a family affair. Boys.

11:23.884 --> 11:25.719
-What's up, Thirsty?
-Lucious.

11:27.220 --> 11:29.422
Here's what we know.

11:29.456 --> 11:32.592
The security firm the Dubois
are using ain't no joke.

11:32.625 --> 11:34.828
They got security,
metal detectors,

11:34.862 --> 11:37.030
bag checks
in all four entrances.

11:37.064 --> 11:40.768
Well, can't we do what we did
in Vegas and, you know,

11:40.801 --> 11:43.436
go through catering,
get Becky on the inside?

11:43.470 --> 11:45.839
No, no, no, all service
employees have been vetted,

11:45.873 --> 11:47.440
even the freakin'
bathroom attendants.

11:47.474 --> 11:49.843
I'm telling you, this place is
locked tight, like a virgin.

11:49.877 --> 11:51.544
Me and Mal walk through
the front doors,

11:51.578 --> 11:52.846
people would notice us.

11:52.880 --> 11:54.948
Do we even know
who's performing?

11:54.982 --> 11:57.851
Yes, she has the ever-lovin'
New York Philharmonic

11:57.885 --> 12:00.220
up in there tonight--
with a guest conductor, though.

12:00.253 --> 12:02.055
I mean, it sounds bootleg to me.

12:02.089 --> 12:04.024
Uh, excuse me, Beethoven.

12:04.057 --> 12:06.059
Uh, you hear us
over here working?

12:06.093 --> 12:08.228
Well, I figured
if y'all wanted to hear from me,

12:08.261 --> 12:09.629
you'd rattle my cage.

12:09.662 --> 12:11.098
Well, if you have
any bright ideas,

12:11.131 --> 12:13.533
now is the time to speak up.

12:13.566 --> 12:18.038
Well, first and foremost,
we're Lyons.

12:18.071 --> 12:19.907
We don't do
the Chutes and Ladders,

12:19.940 --> 12:21.274
Mission: Impossible stuff.

12:21.308 --> 12:23.243
We want to break into a place,

12:23.276 --> 12:26.613
we do that by bustin' heads
straight up with music.

12:26.646 --> 12:29.482
It's music
that gets us in there.

12:32.820 --> 12:35.989
(playing ending arpeggio)

12:36.023 --> 12:38.758
THIRSTY: All right,
let me just get that paperwork.

12:38.792 --> 12:40.828
-(Becky sniffling)
-What's up there, Becky?

12:44.631 --> 12:46.599
Becky, are you, are you crying?

12:46.633 --> 12:48.401
No, I'm-I'm not crying.
I'm fine.

12:48.435 --> 12:50.170
You are crying, man.
What's going on?

12:50.203 --> 12:52.272
I'm not crying.
Leave me alone. I'm good.

12:52.305 --> 12:53.941
Something going on
with the hormones, mama?

12:53.974 --> 12:56.944
Would you...
Don't talk about my hormones!

12:58.711 --> 13:00.680
God.

13:00.713 --> 13:02.682
Okay, I see.

13:02.715 --> 13:04.684
Who's the lucky daddy?

13:07.154 --> 13:09.322
Here.

13:09.356 --> 13:11.324
Come on, take it.

13:11.358 --> 13:13.326
It's gonna be all right.

13:16.696 --> 13:18.665
-(elevator bell dings)
-JAMAL: Yo, Keem,

13:18.698 --> 13:21.501
I swear, I cannot figure
this damn thing out.

13:21.534 --> 13:23.336
It's either getting stuck,

13:23.370 --> 13:26.039
or it just splatters
every-damn-where.

13:26.073 --> 13:28.175
'Cause you never put
the top down tight enough.

13:31.478 --> 13:34.081
How the hell
did you get up in here?

13:35.916 --> 13:38.518
I gave your doorman
$10,000 in cash.

13:38.551 --> 13:41.821
It was... the money
my aunt gave me to leave town.

13:44.724 --> 13:47.194
(exhales)

13:47.227 --> 13:50.030
Wow.

13:50.063 --> 13:52.399
That's what you got
for what you did.

13:54.434 --> 13:58.371
It was supposed to be
a whole lot more...

13:58.405 --> 14:02.042
but I blew it,
because I fell in love with you.

14:02.075 --> 14:04.477
(chuckling):
Oh, well...

14:04.511 --> 14:08.415
let's... let's hear it
for the boy.

14:08.448 --> 14:10.383
What do you want?

14:12.452 --> 14:14.521
I'm not here for pity.

14:14.554 --> 14:16.223
I deserve everything,

14:16.256 --> 14:18.858
every-every broken nose,
every busted lip.

14:18.892 --> 14:21.128
-Yes, you do. -Yes,
everything that you gave me.

14:23.230 --> 14:24.831
But I got some information

14:24.864 --> 14:27.267
that I think you
and your family need to know.

14:27.300 --> 14:29.536
Yeah, well, you can save it.

14:29.569 --> 14:32.239
